cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with stereo estimation and proposes a new method for patch comparison between two feature maps using a convolutional network. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed method uses a novel architecture of convolutional network to learn the matching process. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach for stereo matching that can produce better results than existing methods. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as stereo matching is an important task in robotics for depth perception and obstacle avoidance. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new method for stereo matching that achieves state-of-the-art results on a benchmark dataset.
